== REQUIREMENTS ==

- Rubygems
- activerecord gem
- Ruby-MemCache gem

== INSTALLATION ==

1) Install rubygems (http://www.rubygems.org)

2) Install gems:

$ sudo gem install activerecord Ruby-MemCache

3) Initialize and update the ruby irc library submodule

$ git submodule init
$ git submodule update

4) Copy the config example to a config file:

$ cp config.rb.example config.rb

5) Edit config.rb with your favorite editor, there are comments in the file.

6) Make the sqlite DB:

$ ./makedb.sh

7) Edit the botchk file to reflect your ruby path and rubybot directory.

8) Run the botchk file to load the bot.

$ ./botchk

